name: src/Vec2.js
Vec2
description: A two dimensional vector.

name: fromJSON
description: Creates a Vec2 object from the given plain object.

params.name: json
params.description: The plain object to parse.

params.name: x
params.description: The x-coordinate.

params.name: y
params.description: The y-coordinate.

name: x
description: The x-coordinate.

name: y
description: The y-coordinate.

name: add
description:
Adds another vector to this vector. The original vectors remain
unaffected.

params.name: v
params.description: The vector to add.

params.name: v.x
params.description: The x-coordinate of the vector to add.

params.name: v.y
params.description: The y-coordinate of the vector to add.

name: sub
description:
Subtracts another vector from this vector. The original vectors remain
unaffected.

params.name: v
params.description: The vector to subtract.

params.name: v.x
params.description: The x-coordinate of the vector to subtract.

params.name: v.y
params.description: The y-coordinate of the vector to subtract.

name: mul
description:
Multiplies this vector by a scalar. The original vector remains
unaffected.

params.name: s
params.description: The scalar by which the vector gets multiplied.

return.description: The product of vector and scalar.

name: div
description: Divides this vector by a scalar. The original vector remains unaffected.

params.name: s
params.description: The scalar by which the vector gets divided.

return.description: The quotient of vector and scalar.

name: length
description:
Calculates the length of the vector. The original vector remains
unaffected.

name: normalize
description:
Creates a vector that points in the same direction as the original vector
but has length 1. The original vector remains unaffected.

name: dot
description:
Calculates the dot product of this vector and the given vector. The
original vectors remain unaffected.

params.name: v
params.description: The second vector.

params.name: v.x
params.description: The x-coordinate of the second vector.

params.name: v.y
params.description: The y-coordinate of the second vector.

return.description: The dot product of the two vectors.

name: rotate
description:
Rotates this vector by the given angle. The original vector remains
unaffected.

params.name: alpha
params.description: The angle by which to rotate given in radians.

name: toString
description: Returns a textual representation of this vector.

return.description: A textual representation of this vector.

name: equals
description: Checks if the given vector is equivalent to this one.

params.name: v
params.description: The vector to compare to.

params.name: v.x
params.description: The x-coordinate of the vector to compare to.

params.name: v.y
params.description: The y-coordinate of the vector to compare to.

name: toJSON
description: Serializes this vector.
